






Gold Torrent Inc.

























































Gold Torrent  =  High Grade Gold + Near Term ProductionGold Torrent is a publicly-traded (OTCQB: GTOR) gold mining company with a historic producing high-grade gold project (the "Lucky Shot") located only 75 miles from Anchorage, Alaska. The Lucky Shot project is accessible by road and can be operated all year.Gold Torrent's experienced management and technical team's main focus is to develop and advance the Lucky Shot project. Construction is underway and the project is expected to initiate commercial production in Q4 of 2018 and produce in Phase One 25,000 and Phase Two 50,000 ounces of gold per year at estimated all in sustaining cash cost of $675 per ounce (from the July 2016 NI 43-101 Preliminary Feasibility Study).Gold Torrent continues to look for additional high grade gold opportunities in safe mining jurisdictions and seek ownership in late stage exploration to development-stage  gold mining projects in North America.             


























































































Social Responsibility — Gold Torrent Inc.


















































EnvironmentConserve environmental resources by incorporating environmental protection and rehabilitation during planning stage and project implementationEngage proactively with Government Agencies, the community, and all stakeholders to strictly abide to environmental regulations, laws, and community standardsMaintain a chemical free operation at Lucky Shot MillSocialPerform responsible, and safe extraction and utilization of the available mineral resources, providing jobs and a tax base for local communitiesInform local stakeholders of mining plans and programs, allowing for open communication and feedback regarding safety and environmental policiesMaintain respect and deference to the culture and heritage of the local communitiesGovernanceActively pursue dialog and understanding with the partner communities and other stakeholders in the management of community-based resourcesProvide consultation to partner communities concerning the company's plans and ongoing programsMaintain a high standard for self governance, including high transparency of dealings through independent auditing and complianceEconomicProvide returns for the community and shareholders in a socially and environmentally responsible mannerProvide jobs for local communitiesProvide a tax base for the state and local governments




















