Gold Torrent, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 8:10 PM ET
Metals and Mining

Company Overview of Gold Torrent, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Gold Torrent, Inc. engages in acquisition and exploration of mining properties in the United States. It holds an option to acquire 20% interest in the Willow Creek project, a gold property located in Alaska. The company was formerly known as Celldonate Inc. and changed its name to Gold Torrent, Inc. in January 2014. Gold Torrent, Inc. was founded in 2006 and is based in Boise, Idaho.


960 South Broadway AvenueSuite 530Boise, ID 83706United StatesFounded in 20063 Employees



Phone: 208-343-1413

www.goldtorrentinc.com







Key Executives for Gold Torrent, Inc.




Mr. Daniel J. Kunz B.Sc., MBA, A.A., P.Eng.


      	CEO & Executive Chairman
      


Age: 64
        

Total Annual Compensation: $220.0K








Mr. Ryan Eric Hart


      	President & Director
      


Age: 41
        

Total Annual Compensation: $170.0K








Mr. Alexander Gregory Kunz


      	CFO & Director
      


Age: 33
        

Total Annual Compensation: $95.0K





Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2017. 

Gold Torrent, Inc. Key Developments

Gold Torrent, Inc. Auditor Raises 'Going Concern' Doubt
Jun 23 17
Gold Torrent, Inc. filed its 10-K on Jun 23, 2017 for the period ending Mar 31, 2017. In this report its auditor, Morgan & Company, gave an unqualified opinion expressing doubt that the company can continue as a going concern.


Gold Torrent, Inc. Appoints Patrick M. Okita to the Board of Directors
Feb 17 17
Gold Torrent, Inc. appointed Patrick M. Okita to its Board of Directors effective February 14, 2017. Patrick M. Okita, 57, has served as the Principal and Economic Geologist of Upstream Resources, LLG since its founding in 2000 to the present.


Gold Torrent, Inc. announced delayed 10-Q filing
Aug 16 16
On 08/16/2016, Gold Torrent, Inc. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-Q by the deadline required by the SEC.


